= Overview =
'''The Trailblazers''' are an exploratory group primarily aimed for uncovering hidden dimensions beside the main three. They were founded in [[Level 1]] in November 2006 after the Multi-Dimension Theory surfaced through a post on [[Backchat (Collaborative Log)|Backchat]].

They expand their influence by handing out promotional leaflets, popularizing the theory. This allowed them to increase the number of members by three times to ~1000 throughout two years.

They collect abundant resources such as [[Object 1|Almond Water]], food, and water through communal effort every day. Therefore, they have stored a lot of sustenance for daily uses and emergency situations.

They are hated by other groups in the Backrooms due to their heterodox beliefs. However, they hold a politically neutral stance and refuse to interfere into other groups' policies or conflicts, or respond to their resentment. Therefore, they can become stronger and stronger steadily without disturbance.
= Structure =
The Trailblazers are a self-directed group, but informal leadership still exists in their colonies, maintaining the stability and unity of the group. Despite this, they have established specialized teams <span class="mw-customtoggle-dedicated">dedicated</span> to their respective purposes in order to allocate workload. Positions are filled through self-recommendation, attracting skillful people to join.
= Relations =
The Trailblazers have great influence among ordinary people, but they do not have good relations with other groups due to their unorthodox beliefs. Even so, other groups do not care much about them as they have never been involved in any conflicts.
=<small> M.E.G. </small>=
The Trailblazers had been treated hatefully by the [[M.E.G.]] since their founding, but their hostility died down after a few months because of the lack of conflicts.
=<small> Backroom Colonists </small>=
The [[Backroom Colonists]] remain majority neutral towards the Trailblazers. However, some of their members have shown interest in the goal of discovering a new dimension and even donate supplies to support them.
=<small> Other Groups </small>=
Other groups like the [[Backrooms Investigation Foundation|B.I.F.]] either dismiss the presence of the Trailblazers or show distaste towards them. Nevertheless, no conflicts are fought and the enmity has abated.
= Colonies =
=<small> [[The Starting Point|<span style="color:yellow;text-shadow: 0em 0em 0.5em yellow, 0em 0em 0.5em yellow">The Starting Point</span>]] </small>=
'''The Starting Point''' is the headquarter of the group, spanning 1 km² in [[Level 1]] and housing ~500 people. It serves as the main residence and storage area for group members. It is chosen due to its easy access to exits such as [[The Hub]] and several more.
=<small> [[The Secured Point|<span style="color:yellow;text-shadow: 0em 0em 0.5em yellow, 0em 0em 0.5em yellow">The Secured Point</span>]] </small>=
'''The Secured Point''' is a colony established in [[Level 4]] in January 2007, sheltering ~400 people. It is chosen as a major resource supply because of its plenitude of food and water, its safety, and its strange abundance of exits to [[the Void]], which are believed to be useful for seeking other dimensions.
=<small> [[The Separated Point|<span style="color:yellow;text-shadow: 0em 0em 0.5em yellow, 0em 0em 0.5em yellow">The Separated Point</span>]] </small> =
'''The Separated Point''' is a small outpost consisting of ~100 members, which is formed in March 2008. They are a part of the Megacolony in [[Level 399]], allowing them to spread their influence to more people.<br><br>The progress of finding a new dimension is slow, [[Two Incidents|<span style="color:yellow;text-shadow: 0em 0em 0.5em yellow, 0em 0em 0.5em yellow">until...</span>]]
